CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 7, 1953, pg. 6 reads: "Bond Winner - Curtis B. Haines, Republican chairman of the Fifth Ward and co-boss in YMCA membership campaign, presents a $100 War Bond to J.K. Anderson, biggest individual producer in the drive. Mr. Anderson brought in $389 in memberships.  The War Bond was donated by Clerk Courts Leonard Parsons who "kicked-off" the "Y" drive. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Curtis B. Haines shaking hands with and handing War Bond to J.K. Anderson during Centre Avenue YMCA membership drive, vertical format
